Modified versions of the software may not be published or distributed as part of a new project or product.
2. Distribution
The software may be redistributed or shared in its unmodified form, provided that the following conditions are met:

a. Unmodified Redistribution
Redistribution of the software must be free of charge.
This license must be included with the software to ensure that all recipients understand the terms of use.
The original author's name must remain intact within the software or its associated documentation. Removal or modification of the copyright notice is not permitted.
b. No Distribution of Modified Versions
Modified versions of the software may not be shared or published, whether distributed freely or commercially.
3. Sales and Commercial Use
The sale of the software, whether in its original or modified form, is strictly prohibited.

a. No Commercial Exploitation
You may not sell or commercially exploit the software or any modified version of it.
Any commercial use of the software requires explicit written permission from the original author.
